It's a massive tree, so big you couldn't put your arms around it.

02:25:04.384 --> 02:25:04.848
It is beautiful, green, and alive, like a redwood in California; you could drive a car through it.

02:25:11.850 --> 02:25:31.134
It's planted in the rock, and the water is running out of the tree, coming down the side of the mountain where the man is standing and blowing his horn.

02:25:31.134 --> 02:25:38.000
Now I see two lungs attached outside of a body, breathing in that water.

02:25:38.000 --> 02:25:47.540
These lungs are positioned right underneath that waterfall, and I can see life coming into them.

02:26:07.439 --> 02:26:07.631
I can see the blood flow and the veins, and they are sparkling.

02:26:07.631 --> 02:26:09.119
Why would it be lungs?

02:26:09.119 --> 02:26:10.648
Lord, what is that?

02:26:10.648 --> 02:26:16.349
Why are the lungs breathing like that outside the body?

02:26:22.800 --> 02:26:23.280
The man just sat down on the rock.

02:26:30.160 --> 02:26:35.191
He went from blowing a horn to sitting down to look at the valley, and the water is flowing right by him.

02:26:35.191 --> 02:26:40.740
He's sitting crisscross, looking out over the edge.

02:26:40.740 --> 02:26:44.000
Why is he sitting down now?

02:26:44.000 --> 02:26:56.400
We're seated with him in the heavenlies, far above all principalities.

02:26:56.400 --> 02:27:00.507
It's a place of authority and rest.

02:27:00.507 --> 02:27:04.027
You're not toiling, walking around, or pacing.

02:27:04.027 --> 02:27:08.080
I'm seated because I'm firm in Him and resting.

02:27:09.422 --> 02:27:13.560
That man is taking a seat, looking out over the edge in complete peace, watching the water flow over the people.

02:27:27.840 --> 02:27:28.160
He did what he was supposed to do; he blew his horn and he sat down.

02:27:28.160 --> 02:27:29.770
It's a place of rest.

02:27:29.770 --> 02:27:32.267
Trust confidently in Me.

02:27:45.040 --> 02:27:45.253
I see a peach seed.

02:27:45.253 --> 02:27:57.200
Everything in the kingdom is about seeds: planting the seed and believing for the harvest.

02:27:57.200 --> 02:28:03.253
Let the Word come into you as a seed and it springs forth life.

02:28:03.253 --> 02:28:05.200
Everything revolves around a seed.

02:28:05.200 --> 02:28:12.075
Seed is life, but you have to plant the seed to reap the harvest.

02:28:12.075 --> 02:28:17.984
The Word doesn't return void.

02:28:17.984 --> 02:28:27.753
You're planting the seed of the Word inside your heart, and it springs forth life.

02:28:27.753 --> 02:28:38.898
What was interesting is the seed was covered by blood.

02:28:55.508 --> 02:28:55.714
I could see the peach seed covered in blood as you take your seat.

02:28:57.376 --> 02:28:59.360
It was a split fruit, and the peach seed looked red.

02:29:02.098 --> 02:29:02.649
The Lord said, 'It's covered in the blood.

02:29:02.649 --> 02:29:05.828
' You sow the seed, and I reap the harvest.

02:29:05.828 --> 02:29:07.760
Life is in the Word.

02:29:07.760 --> 02:29:09.360
Seedtime and harvest never cease.

02:29:09.360 --> 02:29:11.980
Whatsoever a man sows, that will he also reap.

02:29:11.980 --> 02:29:17.030
As long as the earth remains, there is seedtime and harvest.

02:29:17.030 --> 02:29:20.319
I believe that's in First Peter, right?

02:29:36.823 --> 02:29:37.040
The flowers wither and the grass fades, but the Word of the Lord will remain forever.

02:29:44.053 --> 02:29:44.347
Thank You, Father, for the blood that covers every seed.

02:29:45.840 --> 02:29:52.846
The seeds we sowed in the past have come to harvest at last.

02:29:52.846 --> 02:30:06.099
Genesis 8:22 says that as long as the earth remains, there will be planting and harvest, cold and heat, summer and winter, day and night; they shall not cease.

02:30:22.640 --> 02:30:23.040
I thank You, Father, for seedtime and harvest tonight.

02:30:23.040 --> 02:30:31.010
We ask for a crop failure over the bad seeds we sowed ignorantly or willingly.

02:30:31.010 --> 02:30:44.368
We repent and call for repentance over those bad seeds, and I thank You, Lord, that they will not bear fruit in our life.

02:30:44.368 --> 02:30:56.240
We call for crop failure over the bad seeds, and we thank You that the good seeds bring forth a thirty, sixty, and hundredfold return in the name of Jesus.

02:30:56.240 --> 02:31:06.399
We call for every bad seed we have sowed to have a crop failure in Jesus' name.

02:31:06.399 --> 02:31:13.577
We call forth abundance to the extreme that overflows over the good seeds and over the man.

02:31:13.577 --> 02:31:23.440
Father, the position of the elder with the long beard—Father, we take our seat.

02:31:23.440 --> 02:31:24.879
Can these bones live?

02:31:24.879 --> 02:31:30.280
Can these bones live?

02:31:30.280 --> 02:31:42.016
We stay in that place of our authority and we take our seat.

02:31:42.016 --> 02:31:44.500
We take our rest.

02:31:44.500 --> 02:31:46.493
We come up higher.

02:31:47.897 --> 02:31:51.400
And we thank you that you have our best in mind, best in heart, Abba.

02:31:51.400 --> 02:31:52.600
We thank you, Lord.

02:31:52.600 --> 02:31:54.100
We thank you, Lord.

02:31:54.100 --> 02:31:54.880
That's interesting.

02:31:54.880 --> 02:31:57.120
Now, I see a fox.

02:31:57.120 --> 02:32:01.190
He's looking to the man on the rock.

02:32:01.190 --> 02:32:08.400
The fox is down below in the valley.

02:32:08.400 --> 02:32:27.040
The fox is looking slyly up toward the man on the rock.

02:32:27.040 --> 02:32:41.547
He has a long bushy tail with a white tip and he's looking up.

02:32:41.547 --> 02:33:11.817
He has a black coal nose, black little coal eyes, and his head is toward the ground.

02:33:11.817 --> 02:33:21.373
But then he looked up at the man sitting on the rock, the fox.

02:33:21.373 --> 02:33:23.780
I see a baby bassinet on wheels.

02:33:35.187 --> 02:33:35.520
It looks like a baby buggy, but on the side where the baby is, it's an old-school 1900s baby bassinet that has an umbrella over the baby.

02:33:48.160 --> 02:33:48.300
I see a white baby gown, white blankets, and all this beautiful white color, and the white is glowing.

02:33:48.300 --> 02:33:52.061
There's a gold trim around the baby basket.

02:33:52.061 --> 02:34:01.120
It's open, but all the trim at the edge of the baby bassinet is gold and it's braided.

02:34:01.120 --> 02:34:08.994
It's welded; it's all meshed together.

02:34:08.994 --> 02:34:17.760
So it's seamless, but it's all like little slits all on it like this.

02:34:17.760 --> 02:34:18.879
And it's gold.

02:34:18.879 --> 02:34:23.394
There are strips of gold going down on this bassinet.

02:34:23.394 --> 02:34:40.240
I see a glorious figure that has no face—a being that has no face, that has a beautiful sparkling gown that's watching over the baby.

02:34:40.240 --> 02:34:54.840
It looks like a veil baby, but he's leaning over looking at the baby with no face and he has a sparkling gown.

02:34:54.840 --> 02:34:59.1000
So the stone is stone.

02:35:13.246 --> 02:35:13.543
We're clothed in His glory.

02:35:13.543 --> 02:35:16.560
Come to Him as a child.

02:35:16.560 --> 02:35:18.399
Come to Him as the baby.

02:35:18.399 --> 02:35:23.488
A baby needs all its needs met by the father or the mother.

02:35:23.488 --> 02:35:26.570
It cannot meet its own needs.

02:35:26.570 --> 02:35:28.559
It's really helpless.

02:35:28.559 --> 02:35:35.160
It's sitting there laying in that bassinet and the father's just doting over his baby.

02:35:40.186 --> 02:35:40.560
The father—the faceless one in glory—is doting over that baby, looking over that child.

02:35:44.415 --> 02:35:47.862
And the baby's just cooing and kicking its little legs, little toes.

02:35:49.585 --> 02:35:51.300
And the daddy's just there.

02:35:51.300 --> 02:36:00.789
I could see the glorious thing—I want to say it's the Lord, I don't know—looking at this baby and the baby's just kicking.

02:36:00.789 --> 02:36:03.154
I can feel the presence.

02:36:03.154 --> 02:36:05.211
He's watching over me.

02:36:05.211 --> 02:36:11.726
He's watching over you or His babies or His children.

02:36:11.726 --> 02:36:14.373
What's that fox doing?

02:36:14.373 --> 02:36:16.507
That's so interesting.

02:36:31.450 --> 02:36:31.620
That is really beautiful.

02:36:31.620 --> 02:36:32.640
We love you, Lord.

02:36:32.640 --> 02:36:34.506
We come to you.

02:36:34.506 --> 02:36:40.208
We're seated with you in the heavenlies, like that old man.

02:36:42.120 --> 02:36:45.359
But we come as babies before the Great I Am—not as adults, but as your babies.

02:36:59.083 --> 02:36:59.359
And we're away from that fox.

02:36:59.359 --> 02:37:01.340
We thank you, Lord.

02:37:01.340 --> 02:37:09.789
We thank you, Father, for that peace as we sit at your feet for the peace that passes understanding.

02:37:10.019 --> 02:37:12.480
The peace that passes all understanding.

02:37:12.480 --> 02:37:14.098
We thank you, Lord.

02:37:14.098 --> 02:37:15.328
We thank you, Lord.

02:37:15.328 --> 02:37:15.744
Hallelujah.

02:37:16.160 --> 02:37:20.259
I see there was a very steep hill for more of you to climb.

02:37:20.259 --> 02:37:22.340
I see a steep hill.

02:37:25.820 --> 02:37:26.120
And the climb has been very intense.

02:37:26.120 --> 02:37:27.320
Push, push, push.

02:37:27.320 --> 02:37:29.040
Climb, climb, climb.

02:37:29.040 --> 02:37:34.569
It's been a long, long road for some of you.

02:37:34.569 --> 02:37:35.947
But the breakthrough—the long, long road.

02:37:35.947 --> 02:37:38.399
You feel like you've been climbing, climbing, climbing.

02:37:38.399 --> 02:37:42.738
'Where are we going to get to the summit?

02:37:42.738 --> 02:37:45.886
' It's all about breaking through for you.

02:37:45.886 --> 02:37:47.577
You've been climbing.

02:37:47.577 --> 02:37:50.169
You're at that place of rest.

02:37:50.169 --> 02:37:54.1000
Your baby is speaking to the dry bones of your life.

02:37:54.1000 --> 02:37:56.107
'Can these bones live?

02:37:56.107 --> 02:37:58.944
' Of your circumstances, of many you have given up on.

02:38:06.926 --> 02:38:08.800
But I hear the Spirit of the Lord say, 'I'm bringing forth life to your circumstances where it seemed the valley of your dry bones were dead and that you are in the valley.

02:38:08.800 --> 02:38:11.085
' But the water's here.

02:38:18.446 --> 02:38:18.731
The birthing is here.

02:38:28.080 --> 02:38:28.400
The baby is here.

02:38:40.936 --> 02:38:41.554
It's the time of the seed that you sowed in the past; you're going to reap the harvest at last.

02:38:41.554 --> 02:38:46.983
Speaking to what you thought was dormant.

02:38:54.590 --> 02:38:54.920
You climb, you climb, you climb.

02:39:02.293 --> 02:39:02.542
I see the people getting weary in well-doing.

02:39:13.973 --> 02:39:14.151
You don't see the manifestation of what you believe for day after day.

02:39:14.506 --> 02:39:18.583
You feel weary in well-doing.

02:39:18.583 --> 02:39:32.120
But when you let go of the rope and you let God—'I'm sitting down, Lord.

02:39:32.120 --> 02:39:33.520
I'm just taking my seat.

02:39:33.520 --> 02:39:35.691
' Can these bones live?

02:39:35.691 --> 02:39:37.679
Can my circumstances change?

02:39:37.679 --> 02:39:41.874
Can my marriage get better?

02:39:41.874 --> 02:39:43.964
Can my kids stop being helens?

02:39:43.964 --> 02:39:45.863
Can, Father, my finances turn around?

02:39:45.863 --> 02:39:51.520
Living from paycheck to paycheck, barely getting by.

02:40:03.680 --> 02:40:03.930
Oh, Father, can these bones live?

02:40:03.930 --> 02:40:08.559
Many of you are the ones standing on the rock.

02:40:08.559 --> 02:40:10.240
Can these bones live?

02:40:10.240 --> 02:40:16.941
My circumstances don't seem to be changing, but the Lord says there's a divine turnaround.

02:40:16.941 --> 02:40:22.959
As long as the earth remains, Genesis—seedtime and harvest doesn't cease.

02:40:22.959 --> 02:40:24.302
Speak to the dry bone.

02:40:24.302 --> 02:40:25.858
Speak to the dead seeds.

02:40:25.858 --> 02:40:26.387
Speak.

02:40:31.690 --> 02:40:31.920
The seeds don't die.

02:40:31.920 --> 02:40:36.027
Don't let the fox come and ruin the vine.

02:40:36.027 --> 02:40:38.399
He's up there.

02:40:38.399 --> 02:40:43.613
What is the fox speaking to you?

02:40:43.613 --> 02:40:46.347
He's lying to you.

02:40:46.347 --> 02:40:49.760
'You're not going to get through this.

02:40:49.760 --> 02:40:52.960
' That's the devil.

02:40:52.960 --> 02:40:57.104
He's trying to eat the vines.

02:41:04.320 --> 02:41:04.800
The small foxes spoil the vines.

02:41:15.000 --> 02:41:15.360
It's the small foxes that are spoiling the vines.

02:41:15.360 --> 02:41:17.880
Don't get weary in well-doing.

02:41:17.880 --> 02:41:23.760
We're not God's adults; we're His children, His babies.

02:41:23.760 --> 02:41:26.503
He's watching over us.

02:41:26.503 --> 02:41:28.160
He has affection.

02:41:28.160 --> 02:41:30.239
His eyes are on the babies.

02:41:30.239 --> 02:41:34.880
We all look like little infants in there kicking our little toes up in our little gown.

02:41:34.880 --> 02:41:38.631
It looked like one of those christening gowns they put on the babies—this beautiful white gown.

02:41:38.631 --> 02:41:46.587
It was glowing with glory, with gold on the bassinet, and He was looking out over that baby.

02:41:48.293 --> 02:41:49.680
The trim was braided.

02:41:49.680 --> 02:41:54.697
He was looking over it with no face.

02:41:54.697 --> 02:41:56.754
He was completely glory.

02:42:04.787 --> 02:42:11.520
I could see no face, but He was looking at the baby and He was watching over the baby.

02:42:12.823 --> 02:42:15.800
And the baby was kicking his little toes up.

02:42:15.800 --> 02:42:20.720
I could see the little feet bouncing up.

02:42:20.720 --> 02:42:23.719
He had little chubby toes.

02:42:23.719 --> 02:42:28.293
He was moving around in that gown.

02:42:36.430 --> 02:42:36.820
It was really beautiful.

02:42:39.022 --> 02:42:39.200
And the Lord is just watching that child.

02:42:40.089 --> 02:42:44.480
And then I saw the seed, and the Lord said those seeds always come to pass.

02:42:44.480 --> 02:42:46.480
Every seed you have in your life.

02:42:55.474 --> 02:42:55.771
The seeds that you sowed in the past will come to harvest at last.

02:42:55.771 --> 02:43:00.440
Believe Me for the seed.

02:43:00.440 --> 02:43:07.726
Believe Me for the manifested crop of the seed.

02:43:07.726 --> 02:43:09.591
Seedtime and harvest doesn't cease.

02:43:09.591 --> 02:43:13.070
Whatsoever a man sows, that will he also reap.

02:43:13.070 --> 02:43:14.320
It doesn't die.

02:43:14.320 --> 02:43:16.880
So call forth your dormant seeds.

02:43:25.467 --> 02:43:26.293
The Lord said they're not dead; they're dormant.

02:43:26.293 --> 02:43:29.600
Speak to them.

02:43:29.600 --> 02:43:40.063
Call forth your dormant seeds and say, "Seeds, grow," and let that river or that water flow out of that mountain over there.

02:43:40.063 --> 02:43:50.080
As long as the earth remains, it's time for you to reap your harvest.

02:43:55.599 --> 02:43:55.759
I call crop failure over my bad ones.

02:44:05.600 --> 02:44:05.991
I said, "Lord, forgive me, but the ones I have in the ground that are good, I'm calling forth the 30, 60, and 100-fold.

02:44:20.799 --> 02:44:21.119
" I want a big harvest.

02:44:21.119 --> 02:44:29.600
Everything you live in life is a seed, a manifestation of a seed.

02:44:29.600 --> 02:44:30.382
Everything.

02:44:35.049 --> 02:44:36.023
What you put inside your heart with the Word of God is seed.

02:44:54.179 --> 02:44:54.399
The sower sows the word.

02:44:54.399 --> 02:44:59.540
Thank you, Father, for tonight's prayer.

02:44:59.540 --> 02:45:04.710
Thank you, Father, that you are watching over our seeds.

02:45:04.710 --> 02:45:07.760
Father, we come to you as babies.

02:45:07.760 --> 02:45:09.333
We are not adults.

02:45:17.040 --> 02:45:17.211
We're sitting there, and we just take our rightful place in the seat and say, "Can these bones live?

02:45:17.211 --> 02:45:19.400
Can our seeds that we've sowed live?

02:45:19.400 --> 02:45:24.400
" Yes, all things are possible to him who believes.

02:45:24.400 --> 02:45:26.696
Don't be weary in well-doing.

02:45:36.200 --> 02:45:36.533
I saw a very steep mountain people were climbing.

02:45:36.533 --> 02:45:40.048
They were resting because they get weary in well-doing.

02:45:40.048 --> 02:45:44.320
They are up there saying, "I am never going to get to the summit.

02:45:44.320 --> 02:45:48.640
We're never going to get to the top.

02:45:48.640 --> 02:45:51.560
We're always going to be climbing this, honey.

02:46:06.450 --> 02:46:06.940
" But they would climb a little bit and then they would rest.

02:46:10.480 --> 02:46:14.759
I could see it was steep as they were trying to get to the top.

02:46:14.759 --> 02:46:17.480
I saw that massive tree on that thing.

02:46:17.480 --> 02:46:19.980
I wonder what that represented.

02:46:19.980 --> 02:46:26.739
Is it like the one where you saw the fire on the seeds?

02:46:26.739 --> 02:46:27.999
Remember the sequoia tree?

02:46:32.149 --> 02:46:32.423
It looked like a sequoia tree, a beautiful sequoia.

02:46:32.423 --> 02:46:34.300
They're saying it's in Ezekiel.

02:46:34.300 --> 02:46:36.800
It's a fruit tree of all kinds.

02:46:36.800 --> 02:46:38.453
That's what they're thinking.

02:46:38.453 --> 02:46:44.630
A fruit tree of all kinds will grow on both banks of the river.

02:46:44.630 --> 02:46:47.991
Their leaves will not wither, nor will their fruit fail.

02:46:47.991 --> 02:46:55.653
Every month they will bear fruit because the water from the sanctuary flows to them.

02:46:55.653 --> 02:46:59.540
Their fruit will serve for food and their leaves for healing.

02:46:59.540 --> 02:47:02.690
Wow, y'all, cool find!

02:47:02.690 --> 02:47:08.418
Ezekiel spoke to the mountain; he spoke to the dry bones.

02:47:08.418 --> 02:47:10.782
But that's the fruit tree.

02:47:10.782 --> 02:47:15.340
I'm going to try to read it, Ezekiel 47.

02:47:28.533 --> 02:47:28.720
I haven't studied it, so my reading might be off.

02:47:41.422 --> 02:47:41.724
"The fruit trees of all kinds will grow on both banks of the river.

02:47:41.724 --> 02:47:47.063
Their leaves will not wither, nor will their fruit fail.

02:47:47.063 --> 02:47:53.504
Every month they will bear fruit because the water from the sanctuary flows to them.

02:47:53.504 --> 02:48:05.429
Their fruit will serve for food and their leaves for healing.

02:48:05.429 --> 02:48:06.914
" That is powerful.

02:48:17.900 --> 02:48:18.200
So he was sitting on the top and that tree came up.

02:48:18.200 --> 02:48:27.268
It was by the river and the water flowed through, and it lines up with what I'm seeing in the scripture of Ezekiel.

02:48:27.268 --> 02:48:28.735
That's cool, huh?

02:48:28.735 --> 02:48:31.850
I was thinking, "What am I seeing all this for?

02:48:34.399 --> 02:48:34.571
" You guys are saying, "Can these bones live?

02:48:34.571 --> 02:48:35.849
" That's what he was saying.

02:48:35.849 --> 02:48:37.342
"Can these bones live?

02:48:37.342 --> 02:48:38.160
" Ezekiel is prophetic.

02:48:38.160 --> 02:48:39.257
Let's read that again.

02:48:39.851 --> 02:48:44.464
I want to read that again; I can't lose that scripture.

02:48:44.464 --> 02:48:49.860
"The fruit trees of all kinds will grow on both banks of the river.

02:48:49.860 --> 02:48:58.499
" He was talking about the fruit of the peach, and it was split before Ezekiel and it was covered in the blood.

02:49:11.067 --> 02:49:11.200
The seed was covered in the blood.

02:49:11.200 --> 02:49:15.702
Fruit trees of all kinds will grow on both banks of the river.

02:49:17.016 --> 02:49:17.448
I only saw one tree.

02:49:17.448 --> 02:49:20.050
"Their leaves will not wither, nor will the fruit fail.

02:49:28.190 --> 02:49:28.460
" You have to move it over, baby.

02:49:28.460 --> 02:49:31.269
"Their leaves will not wither, nor will their fruit fail.

02:49:31.269 --> 02:49:45.680
" So our vine will not cast fruit before its time, just like it says in Deuteronomy.

02:49:45.680 --> 02:49:50.080
Every month they will bear fruit, so you have fruit all the time.

02:50:01.200 --> 02:50:01.349
It's a bountiful supply because the water from the sanctuary flows to them.

02:50:01.349 --> 02:50:04.240
"Their fruit will serve for food and their leaves for healing.

02:50:04.240 --> 02:50:08.133
" Then he gave me Genesis, and I heard him say, "Seedtime and harvest shall never cease.

02:50:19.349 --> 02:50:19.634
" He said speak to it; don't be weary in well-doing as they are climbing the mountain.

02:50:19.634 --> 02:50:23.359
Seeds always produce.

02:50:23.359 --> 02:50:30.080
Even dormant seeds—he said they're not dead seeds—will always produce.

02:50:30.080 --> 02:50:35.279
Speak to them, and that water comes over.

02:50:35.279 --> 02:50:39.097
But the small foxes will ruin the vines.

02:50:42.960 --> 02:50:43.218
I wonder what that means.

